					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-9475147#post-4092706</guid>
				<title>Author Post</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-9475147/the-grove-of-exiles#post-4092706</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 19 Dec 2018 23:55:21 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>TechSorcerer2747</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2921100</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>The views and opinions within this entry do not reflect those of the author, and should not under any circumstances be subject to a Freudian interpretation about his relationship with his own mother.</p> <p>I realize this is dense, lore-heavy, and probably steps on a lot of toes regarding people's headcanons, but I'm happy with how it turned out. A huge thank you to <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/salamander724" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1486450&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1545267491" alt="Salamander724" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1486450)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/salamander724" >Salamander724</a></span> from SCP-KO, without whom this would not have been possible, and to<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/zyn" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1404533&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1545267491" alt="Zyn" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1404533)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/zyn" >Zyn</a></span>, who, as always, provides excellent feedback.</p> <div class="collapsible-block"> <div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">&quot;Hey,&nbsp;you're&nbsp;just&nbsp;trying&nbsp;to&nbsp;shoe-horn&nbsp;in&nbsp;a&nbsp;new&nbsp;GoI,&nbsp;aren't&nbsp;you?&quot;</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none"> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Yes&nbsp;and&nbsp;No</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-content"> <p>Uh, sort of. While the idea of the Children is something I'd love to expand upon, one that's been in my head for a while, this article and the idea of Name-based anomalies kind of hinges on them being the Children of the <em>Nameless</em> Queen. If it picks up traction, great. If not, I feel like there's a lot said about them here, and a lot of questions left to answer, which is fine by me.</p> </div> </div> </div> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
